children.subject: Sorry, I've also taken 188, just updated the post. I was doing average in cs70, from what I heard about ee126 the workload and difficulty are really high, if there's a huge jump compared to cs70 I'd rather take stat140.

<md>the workload of 126 has decreased significantly imo when I took it, no where near the legendary tier difficulty it used to be. Taking it is much less painful these days. Probably okay with cs 170 and cs 161 </md>
CS188 is on the lighter side of the CS upper division classes. If 126 is still open, I’d recommend that for preparing for 189.

history.content: I'm currently enrolled in 170,161 and an art breadth. I originally planed to take stat 140 to get prepared for 189, but Prof. Adhikari is not teaching next semester and many have suggested me to hold off for one semester for this reason. As an incoming third year, I need some time to prepare for interviews and recruiting, is there any good choice of a third cs upper div that could take with 170+161 while still allow me to have a manageable schedule? (I have taken 186, 188, data100)
